    public final class EntityHistoryAggregate
extends Aggregate<EntityHistoryId,EntityHistory,EntityHistoryVBuilder>
    The aggregate which manages the history of a single entity.

    Each Aggregate, Projection, and ProcessManager in the system has a corresponding entity history.

    The history of this aggregate has the knowledge about all the messages ever dispatched to the associated entity.

    An EntityHistory gives the record-based entities (such as Projections and ProcessManagers) traits of an event-sourced entity. For instance, with the help of EntityHistory the history of a record-based entity can be investigated and manipulated. The major use case for this facility is implementing idempotent message handlers.

    This aggregate belongs to the System bounded context. The aggregate doesn't have an own entity history.
